{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843888577,"sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","part":{"id":"prt_d788b38ae0016IvkTztyOni3wi","messageID":"msg_d788b2b55001DKCzdCqnf7erCq","sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d977e63f7c904cefa977711a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the Sandbox creation processor within the WorkloadManager module for the AgentCube platform. The Sandbox processor is responsible for creating and managing sandboxed execution environments where agent runtimes execute their workloads.\n6: \n7: The Sandbox processor provides:\n8: \n9: - **Sandbox lifecycle management** — Create, configure, and destroy sandbox environments\n10: - **Resource isolation** — Enforce resource quotas and network policies per sandbox\n11: - **Kubernetes-native implementation** — Deploy sandboxes as Kubernetes pods with appropriate security contexts\n12: - **Status synchronization** — Update AgentRuntime status based on sandbox state\n13: - **Cleanup orchestration** — Handle graceful termination and resource cleanup\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Sandbox Processor Interface** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox.go`)\n24:    - `SandboxProcessor` interface definition\n25:    - `Create`, `Delete`, `Get`, `Update` methods\n26:    - Configuration options for sandbox creation\n27: \n28: 2. **Sandbox Builder** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_builder.go`)\n29:    - Pod spec construction from AgentRuntime spec\n30:    - Security context configuration\n31:    - Resource quota enforcement\n32:    - Network policy application\n33: \n34: 3. **Sandbox Configurator** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_configurator.go`)\n35:    - Isolation boundary setup\n36:    - Environment variable injection\n37:    - Volume mount configuration\n38:    - Health check probes setup\n39: \n40: 4. **Resource Allocator** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/resource_allocator.go`)\n41:    - CPU/memory quota enforcement\n42:    - Storage allocation\n43:    - Resource tracking and reporting\n44: \n45: 5. **Sandbox Status Monitor** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_status.go`)\n46:    - Pod status polling\n47:    - Condition updates\n48:    - Phase transition logic\n49: \n50: 6. **Integration with AgentRuntime Handler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/agent_runtime.go`)\n51:    - Trigger sandbox creation on AgentRuntime create\n52:    - Handle sandbox deletion on AgentRuntime delete\n53:    - Status synchronization on update\n54: \n55: ### Out of Scope\n56: \n57: - WebSocket proxying to sandboxes (deferred to router component)\n58: - CLI command implementations (Python SDK task)\n59: - Controller/reconciler loop (separate controller component)\n60: - Multi-namespace sandbox orchestration (future enhancement)\n61: - Custom sandbox image management (uses images from AgentRuntime spec)\n62: \n63: ## Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### Dependencies\n66: \n67: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n68: |------------|------|--------|\n69: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Generated Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime |\n70: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | Core Kubernetes client for Pod operations |\n71: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | Pod, Container, ResourceQuota types |\n72: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource` | Required | Resource quantity parsing |\n73: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Required | AgentRuntime types |\n74: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Required | MetaV1 types (ObjectMeta, etc.) |\n75: | `k8s.io/utils/pointer` | Optional | Pointer utilities |\n76: \n77: ### Downstream Consumers\n78: \n79: 1. **AgentRuntime Handler**: Primary consumer of Sandbox processor\n80: 2. **CodeInterpreter Handler**: May use sandbox processor for interpreter isolation\n81: 3. **Controller (future)**: Will use processor for reconciliation logic\n82: 4. **Router**: May query sandbox status for routing decisions\n83: 5. **Python SDK**: Indirect consumer via WorkloadManager HTTP API\n84: \n85: ### Breaking Changes\n86: \n87: None — this is the initial implementation.\n88: \n89: ### Migration Path\n90: \n91: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future migrations may include:\n92: - Sandbox spec versioning (`SandboxTemplateSpec` v1 → v2)\n93: - Security context hardening (breaking change requiring pod recreation)\n94: - Resource quota model changes (may require sandbox recreation)\n95: \n96: ## Alternatives Considered\n97: \n98: ### Alternative 1: Use Kubernetes Jobs instead of Pods\n99: \n100: **Approach:** Deploy sandboxes as Kubernetes Jobs with restart policy.\n101: \n102: **Pros:**\n103: - Built-in completion tracking\n104: - Automatic retry on failure\n105: - Standard Kubernetes primitive\n106: \n107: **Cons:**\n108: - Jobs are designed for batch workloads, not long-running services\n109: - More complex status management\n110: - Harder to inject dynamic configuration\n111: - Overhead of Job controller\n112: \n113: **Decision:** Rejected. Agent runtimes are long-running services; Pods provide simpler lifecycle management.\n114: \n115: ### Alternative 2: Use StatefulSets for Sandboxes\n116: \n117: **Approach:** Deploy each sandbox as a StatefulSet with replicas=1.\n118: \n119: **Pros:**\n120: - Stable network identity\n121: - Persistent volume claims\n122: - Ordered deployment\n123: \n124: **Cons:**\n125: - Over-engineering for single-pod workloads\n126: - Slower creation/deletion\n127: - More complex resource tracking\n128: - Unnecessary for stateless sandboxes\n129: \n130: **Decision:** Rejected. StatefulSets add unnecessary complexity; plain Pods with dynamic configuration are sufficient.\n131: \n132: ### Alternative 3: Use containerd/shim directly\n133: \n134: **Approach:** Bypass Kubernetes and create containers directly via containerd API.\n135: \n136: **Pros:**\n137: - Faster container startup\n138: - Direct control over container runtime\n139: - No Kubernetes API overhead\n140: \n141: **Cons:**\n142: - Loses Kubernetes-native benefits (scheduling, resource management)\n143: - Must implement own scheduling logic\n144: - Harder to integrate with Kubernetes RBAC\n145: - Additional operational complexity\n146: \n147: **Decision:** Rejected. Kubernetes-native approach aligns with AgentCube architecture and leverages existing cluster infrastructure.\n148: \n149: ### Alternative 4: Use gVisor or Kata Containers for isolation\n150: \n151: **Approach:** Deploy sandboxes with runtime-class for enhanced isolation.\n152: \n153: **Pros:**\n154: - Stronger security isolation\n155: - Kernel-level separation\n156: - Better multi-tenant security\n157: \n158: **Cons:**\n159: - Requires cluster-wide runtime-class configuration\n160: - Performance overhead\n161: - Not all clusters support custom runtimes\n162: - Added complexity for initial implementation\n163: \n164: **Decision:** Defer to future enhancement. Start with standard Kubernetes security contexts; can add runtime-class support via configuration later.\n165: \n166: ### Alternative 5: Embed sandbox logic in AgentRuntime controller\n167: \n168: **Approach:** Keep sandbox creation inside controller reconcile loop.\n169: \n170: **Pros:**\n171: - Tighter integration with AgentRuntime lifecycle\n172: - Single place for all logic\n173: - No additional HTTP layer\n174: \n175: **Cons:**\n176: - Couples HTTP API to controller logic\n177: - Harder to test sandbox creation independently\n178: - Controller becomes bloated\n179: - Violates separation of concerns\n180: \n181: **Decision:** Rejected. WorkloadManager processor pattern provides cleaner separation and enables independent testing/scaling.\n182: \n183: ## Implementation Plan\n184: \n185: 1. **Define Sandbox Processor Interface** (`processor/sandbox.go`)\n186:    ```go\n187:    type SandboxProcessor interface {\n188:        Create(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*SandboxResult, error)\n189:        Delete(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n190:        Get(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*SandboxStatus, error)\n191:        Update(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*SandboxResult, error)\n192:    }\n193:    ```\n194: \n195: 2. **Implement Sandbox Builder** (`processor/sandbox_builder.go`)\n196:    - Convert AgentRuntime spec to Pod spec\n197:    - Apply security contexts\n198:    - Configure resource limits\n199:    - Set up probes\n200: \n201: 3. **Implement Resource Allocator** (`processor/resource_allocator.go`)\n202:    - Parse ResourceQuota from AgentRuntime spec\n203:    - Validate against namespace quotas\n204:    - Apply limits to pod spec\n205: \n206: 4. **Implement Sandbox Configurator** (`processor/sandbox_configurator.go`)\n207:    - Inject environment variables\n208:    - Configure volumes\n209:    - Set up network policies\n210: \n211: 5. **Implement Sandbox Status Monitor** (`processor/sandbox_status.go`)\n212:    - Poll pod status\n213:    - Update conditions\n214:    - Handle phase transitions\n215: \n216: 6. **Integrate with AgentRuntime Handler** (`handler/agent_runtime.go`)\n217:    - Call sandbox processor in CreateAgentRuntime\n218:    - Call sandbox processor in DeleteAgentRuntime\n219:    - Add status sync endpoint\n220: \n221: 7. **Write Unit Tests**\n222:    - Sandbox builder tests with mock AgentRuntime\n223:    - Resource allocator tests with various quota configs\n224:    - Status monitor tests with fake pod informer\n225: \n226: 8. **Write Integration Tests**\n227:    - End-to-end sandbox creation with test K8s cluster\n228:    - Resource quota enforcement tests\n229:    - Network policy application tests\n230: \n231: ## Sandbox Architecture\n232: \n233: ### Pod Spec Structure\n234: \n235: ```yaml\n236: apiVersion: v1\n237: kind: Pod\n238: metadata:\n239:   name: <agentruntime-name>-sandbox\n240:   namespace: <agentruntime-namespace>\n241:   labels:\n242:     agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <agentruntime-name>\n243:     agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox: \"true\"\n244: spec:\n245:   securityContext:\n246:     runAsNonRoot: true\n247:     runAsUser: 1000\n248:     fsGroup: 1000\n249:   containers:\n250:   - name: sandbox\n251:     image: <from AgentRuntime spec>\n252:     command: [from spec]\n253:     args: [from spec]\n254:     env: [injected from spec + system vars]\n255:     resources:\n256:       limits:\n257:         cpu: <from ResourceQuota>\n258:         memory: <from ResourceQuota>\n259:       requests:\n260:         cpu: <calculated>\n261:         memory: <calculated>\n262:     securityContext:\n263:       allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n264:       readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n265:       capabilities:\n266:         drop: [\"ALL\"]\n267:     livenessProbe:\n268:       httpGet:\n269:         path: /healthz\n270:         port: 8080\n271:       initialDelaySeconds: 5\n272:       periodSeconds: 10\n273:     readinessProbe:\n274:       httpGet:\n275:         path: /ready\n276:         port: 8080\n277:       initialDelaySeconds: 3\n278:       periodSeconds: 5\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ### Resource Allocation Strategy\n282: \n283: 1. **CPU**: Use `ResourceQuota.CPU` as limit, 50% of limit as request\n284: 2. **Memory**: Use `ResourceQuota.Memory` as limit, 70% of limit as request\n285: 3. **Storage**: Mount ephemeral storage with `ResourceQuota.Storage` limit\n286: \n287: ### Security Hardening\n288: \n289: 1. **Non-root user**: Always run as UID 1000\n290: 2. **Read-only root filesystem**: Prevent runtime modifications\n291: 3. **Drop capabilities**: Remove all Linux capabilities\n292: 4. **No privilege escalation**: Block setuid/setgid binaries\n293: 5. **Network policies**: Default deny, explicit allow rules from spec\n294: \n295: ## API Extension\n296: \n297: ### New Endpoints\n298: \n299: | Method | Path | Description |\n300: |--------|------|-------------|\n301: | `POST` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` | Trigger sandbox creation |\n302: | `GET` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` | Get sandbox status |\n303: | `DELETE` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` | Delete sandbox |\n304: | `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | List all sandboxes (admin) |\n305: \n306: ### Response Format\n307: \n308: **Sandbox Status Response:**\n309: ```json\n310: {\n311:   \"name\": \"my-runtime-sandbox\",\n312:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n313:   \"phase\": \"Running\",\n314:   \"podName\": \"my-runtime-sandbox-abc123\",\n315:   \"podIP\": \"10.244.1.5\",\n316:   \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T00:00:00Z\",\n317:   \"conditions\": [\n318:     {\n319:       \"type\": \"Ready\",\n320:       \"status\": \"True\",\n321:       \"reason\": \"PodReady\",\n322:       \"message\": \"Sandbox pod is ready\"\n323:     }\n324:   ],\n325:   \"resources\": {\n326:     \"cpuLimit\": \"1\",\n327:     \"memoryLimit\": \"512Mi\",\n328:     \"storageLimit\": \"1Gi\"\n329:   }\n330: }\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ## Success Criteria\n334: \n335: - [ ] SandboxProcessor interface defined and documented\n336: - [ ] Sandbox builder creates valid pod specs from AgentRuntime\n337: - [ ] Resource quotas are enforced (CPU, memory, storage)\n338: - [ ] Security contexts applied correctly (non-root, read-only, no caps)\n339: - [ ] Network policies configured from AgentRuntime spec\n340: - [ ] Sandbox status syncs to AgentRuntime status\n341: - [ ] Unit tests cover all processor methods (>80% coverage)\n342: - [ ] Integration tests pass with test K8s cluster\n343: - [ ] Sandbox cleanup on AgentRuntime deletion\n344: - [ ] Error handling for all failure scenarios (quota exceeded, image pull errors, etc.)\n345: \n346: ## Testing Strategy\n347: \n348: ### Unit Tests\n349: \n350: 1. **SandboxBuilder Tests**\n351:    - Test pod spec generation with minimal AgentRuntime spec\n352:    - Test pod spec generation with full AgentRuntime spec\n353:    - Test security context application\n354:    - Test resource limit application\n355: \n356: 2. **ResourceAllocator Tests**\n357:    - Test quota parsing and validation\n358:    - Test quota enforcement (success and failure cases)\n359:    - Test default quota application when not specified\n360: \n361: 3. **SandboxProcessor Tests**\n362:    - Test Create() with valid AgentRuntime\n363:    - Test Create() with invalid spec (missing image)\n364:    - Test Delete() with existing sandbox\n365:    - Test Delete() with non-existent sandbox\n366:    - Test Get() status retrieval\n367:    - Test Update() resource changes\n368: \n369: ### Integration Tests\n370: \n371: 1. **Sandbox Creation Flow**\n372:    - Create AgentRuntime via HTTP API\n373:    - Verify sandbox pod created in K8s\n374:    - Verify pod has correct labels/annotations\n375:    - Verify resource limits applied\n376: \n377: 2. **Sandbox Deletion Flow**\n378:    - Delete AgentRuntime via HTTP API\n379:    - Verify sandbox pod deleted\n380:    - Verify cleanup completes within timeout\n381: \n382: 3. **Status Synchronization**\n383:    - Verify AgentRuntime status updates when sandbox starts\n384:    - Verify AgentRuntime status updates when sandbox becomes ready\n385:    - Verify conditions are correctly populated\n386: \n387: ## Risks and Mitigations\n388: \n389: | Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n390: |------|--------|------------|------------|\n391: | Resource quota conflicts | Medium | Medium | Validate quotas before pod creation; return clear error messages |\n392: | Pod stuck in Pending | Medium | Medium | Add timeout handling; provide diagnostic info in status |\n393: | Security context misconfiguration | High | Low | Use hardened defaults; add validation tests |\n394: | Sandbox cleanup failures | Medium | Low | Implement finalizer-based cleanup; add retry logic |\n395: | Network policy not applied | High | Medium | Test with network policy conformance tests; add fallback deny-all |\n396: \n397: ## Future Considerations\n398: \n399: 1. **Runtime Class Support**: Add `runtimeClassName` field to AgentRuntime spec for gVisor/Kata\n400: 2. **Persistent Volumes**: Support volume claims for stateful sandboxes\n401: 3. **Sandbox Pooling**: Pre-create sandbox pool for faster startup\n402: 4. **Multi-container Sandboxes**: Support sidecar containers (logging, monitoring)\n403: 5. **Custom Scheduling**: Add node selector/affinity/tolerations to AgentRuntime spec\n404: 6. **Sandbox Snapshots**: Support checkpoint/restore for long-running sandboxes\n405: \n406: ## References\n407: \n408: - [Kubernetes Pods](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/)\n409: - [Kubernetes Security Context](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/security-context/)\n410: - [Kubernetes Resource Management](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/manage-resources-containers/)\n411: - [Kubernetes Network Policies](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/network-policies/)\n412: - Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n413: - Related: `changes/AR-004/` (WorkloadManager HTTP Service)\n414: - Related: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 414 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Sandbox creation processor within the WorkloadManager module for the AgentCube platform. The Sandbox processor is responsible for creating and managing sandboxed execution environments where agent runtimes execute their workloads.\n\nThe Sandbox processor provides:\n\n- **Sandbox lifecycle management** — Create, configure, and destroy sandbox environments\n- **Resource isolation** — Enforce resource quotas and network policies per sandbox\n- **Kubernetes-native implementation** — Deploy sandboxes as Kubernetes pods with appropriate security contexts\n- **Status synchronization** — Update AgentRuntime status based on sandbox state\n- **Cleanup orchestration** — Handle graceful termination and resource cleanup\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775843888553,"end":1775843888574}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843888579,"sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","part":{"id":"prt_d788b4937001pTR3ahK3d5Q3z3","messageID":"msg_d788b2b55001DKCzdCqnf7erCq","sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_94a6773ccedc462e8a4655c2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n5: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n6: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n7: \tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n8: \n9: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n10: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n11: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/middleware\"\n12: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n13: )\n14: \n15: type Dependencies struct {\n16: \tClient    dynamic.Interface\n17: \tK8sClient kubernetes.Interface\n18: \tPodLister corev1lister.PodLister\n19: \tARLister  processor.AgentRuntimeLister\n20: \tCILister  processor.CodeInterpreterLister\n21: }\n22: \n23: func SetupRoutes(engine *gin.Engine, deps *Dependencies, health *handler.HealthHandler) {\n24: \tengine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n25: \tengine.Use(gin.Logger())\n26: \tengine.Use(middleware.RequestIDMiddleware())\n27: \n28: \tengine.GET(\"/healthz\", health.HealthzHandler)\n29: \tengine.GET(\"/readyz\", health.ReadyzHandler)\n30: \n31: \tarGroup := engine.Group(\"/api/v1/agentruntimes\")\n32: \t{\n33: \t\tarHandler := handler.NewAgentRuntimeHandler(deps.Client)\n34: \t\tarGroup.POST(\"\", arHandler.CreateAgentRuntime)\n35: \t\tarGroup.GET(\"\", arHandler.ListAgentRuntimes)\n36: \t\tarGroup.GET(\"/:name\", arHandler.GetAgentRuntime)\n37: \t\tarGroup.PUT(\"/:name\", arHandler.UpdateAgentRuntime)\n38: \t\tarGroup.DELETE(\"/:name\", arHandler.DeleteAgentRuntime)\n39: \t}\n40: \n41: \tciGroup := engine.Group(\"/api/v1/codeinterpreters\")\n42: \t{\n43: \t\tciHandler := handler.NewCodeInterpreterHandler(deps.Client)\n44: \t\tciGroup.POST(\"\", ciHandler.CreateCodeInterpreter)\n45: \t\tciGroup.GET(\"\", ciHandler.ListCodeInterpreters)\n46: \t\tciGroup.GET(\"/:name\", ciHandler.GetCodeInterpreter)\n47: \t\tciGroup.PUT(\"/:name\", ciHandler.UpdateCodeInterpreter)\n48: \t\tciGroup.DELETE(\"/:name\", ciHandler.DeleteCodeInterpreter)\n49: \t}\n50: \n51: \tsandboxGroup := engine.Group(\"/v1\")\n52: \t{\n53: \t\tsandboxHandler := handler.NewSandboxHandler(\n54: \t\t\tdeps.Client,\n55: \t\t\tdeps.K8sClient,\n56: \t\t\tdeps.PodLister,\n57: \t\t\tdeps.ARLister,\n58: \t\t\tdeps.CILister,\n59: \t\t\t\"default\",\n60: \t\t)\n61: \t\tsandboxGroup.POST(\"/agent-runtime\", sandboxHandler.HandleAgentRuntimeCreate)\n62: \t\tsandboxGroup.POST(\"/code-interpreter\", sandboxHandler.HandleCodeInterpreterCreate)\n63: \t}\n64: }\n65: \n66: type informerListerAdapter struct {\n67: \tinformer runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\n68: }\n69: \n70: func (a *informerListerAdapter) AgentRuntimes(namespace string) processor.AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister {\n71: \treturn a.informer.Lister().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n72: }\n73: \n74: type codeInterpreterListerAdapter struct {\n75: \tinformer runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n76: }\n77: \n78: func (a *codeInterpreterListerAdapter) CodeInterpreters(namespace string) processor.CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister {\n79: \treturn a.informer.Lister().CodeInterpreters(namespace)\n80: }\n\n(End of file - total 80 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n\n\truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/middleware\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n)\n\ntype Dependencies struct {\n\tClient    dynamic.Interface\n\tK8sClient kubernetes.Interface\n\tPodLister corev1lister.PodLister\n\tARLister  processor.AgentRuntimeLister\n\tCILister  processor.CodeInterpreterLister","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go","time":{"start":1775843888560,"end":1775843888577}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843888582,"sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","part":{"id":"prt_d788b3e1a001q5cZmrX25hCrew","messageID":"msg_d788b2b55001DKCzdCqnf7erCq","sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e5cf0b3767b7473aa6aac55e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package handler\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"net/http\"\n5: \n6: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n7: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n8: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n9: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n10: \tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n11: \n12: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n13: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response\"\n14: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n15: )\n16: \n17: type SandboxHandler struct {\n18: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n19: \tk8sClient     kubernetes.Interface\n20: \tpodLister     corev1lister.PodLister\n21: \tarLister      processor.AgentRuntimeLister\n22: \tciLister      processor.CodeInterpreterLister\n23: \tnamespace     string\n24: }\n25: \n26: func NewSandboxHandler(\n27: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n28: \tk8sClient kubernetes.Interface,\n29: \tpodLister corev1lister.PodLister,\n30: \tarLister processor.AgentRuntimeLister,\n31: \tciLister processor.CodeInterpreterLister,\n32: \tnamespace string,\n33: ) *SandboxHandler {\n34: \treturn &SandboxHandler{\n35: \t\tdynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n36: \t\tk8sClient:     k8sClient,\n37: \t\tpodLister:     podLister,\n38: \t\tarLister:      arLister,\n39: \t\tciLister:      ciLister,\n40: \t\tnamespace:     namespace,\n41: \t}\n42: }\n43: \n44: func (h *SandboxHandler) HandleAgentRuntimeCreate(c *gin.Context) {\n45: \tvar req types.CreateSandboxRequest\n46: \tif err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n47: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40002, \"Invalid request body\")\n48: \t\treturn\n49: \t}\n50: \n51: \tif err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n52: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40003, err.Error())\n53: \t\treturn\n54: \t}\n55: \n56: \treq.Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"\n57: \n58: \truntime, err := processor.GetAgentRuntime(h.arLister, req.Namespace, req.Name)\n59: \tif err != nil {\n60: \t\tif err == processor.ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound {\n61: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusNotFound, 40401, \"agent runtime not found\")\n62: \t\t\treturn\n63: \t\t}\n64: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n65: \t\treturn\n66: \t}\n67: \n68: \tproc := processor.NewSandboxProcessor(h.dynamicClient, h.k8sClient, h.podLister, h.arLister, h.ciLister, h.namespace)\n69: \n70: \tsessionID, err := proc.GenerateSessionID()\n71: \tif err != nil {\n72: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n73: \t\treturn\n74: \t}\n75: \n76: \tsandbox, err := proc.BuildSandboxObject(runtime, sessionID)\n77: \tif err != nil {\n78: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n79: \t\treturn\n80: \t}\n81: \n82: \tuserClient := h.dynamicClient.Resource(processor.SandboxGVR).Namespace(runtime.Namespace)\n83: \n84: \tinfo, err := proc.CreateSandbox(c.Request.Context(), sandbox, false, userClient, sessionID)\n85: \tif err != nil {\n86: \t\tif err == processor.ErrSandboxCreationTimeout {\n87: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n88: \t\t\treturn\n89: \t\t}\n90: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n91: \t\treturn\n92: \t}\n93: \n94: \tresp := types.CreateSandboxResponse{\n95: \t\tSessionID:   info.SessionID,\n96: \t\tSandboxID:   info.SandboxID,\n97: \t\tSandboxName: info.SandboxName,\n98: \t\tEntryPoints: info.EntryPoints,\n99: \t}\n100: \n101: \tresponse.JSON(c, http.StatusOK, resp)\n102: }\n103: \n104: func (h *SandboxHandler) HandleCodeInterpreterCreate(c *gin.Context) {\n105: \tvar req types.CreateSandboxRequest\n106: \tif err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n107: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40002, \"Invalid request body\")\n108: \t\treturn\n109: \t}\n110: \n111: \tif err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n112: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40003, err.Error())\n113: \t\treturn\n114: \t}\n115: \n116: \treq.Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n117: \n118: \tinterpreter, err := processor.GetCodeInterpreter(h.ciLister, req.Namespace, req.Name)\n119: \tif err != nil {\n120: \t\tif err == processor.ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound {\n121: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusNotFound, 40401, \"code interpreter not found\")\n122: \t\t\treturn\n123: \t\t}\n124: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n125: \t\treturn\n126: \t}\n127: \n128: \tproc := processor.NewSandboxProcessor(h.dynamicClient, h.k8sClient, h.podLister, h.arLister, h.ciLister, h.namespace)\n129: \n130: \tsessionID, err := proc.GenerateSessionID()\n131: \tif err != nil {\n132: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n133: \t\treturn\n134: \t}\n135: \n136: \tvar sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured\n137: \tisWarmPool := false\n138: \n139: \tsandbox, err = proc.BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox(interpreter, sessionID)\n140: \tif err != nil {\n141: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n142: \t\treturn\n143: \t}\n144: \n145: \tuserClient := h.dynamicClient.Resource(processor.SandboxGVR).Namespace(interpreter.Namespace)\n146: \n147: \tinfo, err := proc.CreateSandbox(c.Request.Context(), sandbox, isWarmPool, userClient, sessionID)\n148: \tif err != nil {\n149: \t\tif err == processor.ErrSandboxCreationTimeout {\n150: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n151: \t\t\treturn\n152: \t\t}\n153: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n154: \t\treturn\n155: \t}\n156: \n157: \tresp := types.CreateSandboxResponse{\n158: \t\tSessionID:   info.SessionID,\n159: \t\tSandboxID:   info.SandboxID,\n160: \t\tSandboxName: info.SandboxName,\n161: \t\tEntryPoints: info.EntryPoints,\n162: \t}\n163: \n164: \tresponse.JSON(c, http.StatusOK, resp)\n165: }\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package handler\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n)\n\ntype SandboxHandler struct {\n\tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n\tk8sClient     kubernetes.Interface\n\tpodLister     corev1lister.PodLister","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go","time":{"start":1775843888556,"end":1775843888580}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843888585,"sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","part":{"id":"prt_d788b43bb0018kPpJOUmM6drzb","messageID":"msg_d788b2b55001DKCzdCqnf7erCq","sessionID":"ses_2877500fbffe2ry268eDmqDR9H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_63e90ea12f9544359eec1e65","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package processor\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"crypto/rand\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"math/big\"\n8: \t\"net\"\n9: \t\"strings\"\n10: \t\"time\"\n11: \n12: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n13: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n15: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/labels\"\n16: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n17: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n18: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n19: \tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n20: \n21: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n22: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n23: )\n24: \n25: var (\n26: \tSandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n27: \t\tGroup:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n28: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n29: \t\tResource: \"sandboxes\",\n30: \t}\n31: \n32: \tSandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n33: \t\tGroup:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n34: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n35: \t\tResource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n36: \t}\n37: )\n38: \n39: const (\n40: \tSessionIDLabelKey        = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n41: \tIdleTimeoutAnnotation    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n42: \tSandboxNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n43: \tSandboxPodNameAnnotation = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n44: )\n45: \n46: var (\n47: \tErrAgentRuntimeNotFound    = fmt.Errorf(\"agent runtime not found\")\n48: \tErrCodeInterpreterNotFound = fmt.Errorf(\"code interpreter not found\")\n49: \tErrTemplateMissing         = fmt.Errorf(\"template is missing\")\n50: \tErrSandboxCreationTimeout  = fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n51: )\n52: \n53: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n54: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n55: }\n56: \n57: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n58: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: }\n60: \n61: type CodeInterpreterLister interface {\n62: \tCodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister\n63: }\n64: \n65: type CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister interface {\n66: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n67: }\n68: \n69: type SandboxProcessor struct {\n70: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n71: \tk8sClient     kubernetes.Interface\n72: \tpodLister     corev1lister.PodLister\n73: \tarLister      AgentRuntimeLister\n74: \tciLister      CodeInterpreterLister\n75: \tnamespace     string\n76: }\n77: \n78: func NewSandboxProcessor(\n79: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n80: \tk8sClient kubernetes.Interface,\n81: \tpodLister corev1lister.PodLister,\n82: \tarLister AgentRuntimeLister,\n83: \tciLister CodeInterpreterLister,\n84: \tnamespace string,\n85: ) *SandboxProcessor {\n86: \treturn &SandboxProcessor{\n87: \t\tdynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n88: \t\tk8sClient:     k8sClient,\n89: \t\tpodLister:     podLister,\n90: \t\tarLister:      arLister,\n91: \t\tciLister:      ciLister,\n92: \t\tnamespace:     namespace,\n93: \t}\n94: }\n95: \n96: func RandString(n int) (string, error) {\n97: \tconst letters = \"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\"\n98: \tresult := make([]byte, n)\n99: \tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n100: \t\tnum, err := rand.Int(rand.Reader, big.NewInt(int64(len(letters))))\n101: \t\tif err != nil {\n102: \t\t\treturn \"\", err\n103: \t\t}\n104: \t\tresult[i] = letters[num.Int64()]\n105: \t}\n106: \treturn string(result), nil\n107: }\n108: \n109: func (p *SandboxProcessor) GenerateSessionID() (string, error) {\n110: \tid, err := rand.Int(rand.Reader, big.NewInt(1e18))\n111: \tif err != nil {\n112: \t\treturn \"\", err\n113: \t}\n114: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%018d\", id.Int64()), nil\n115: }\n116: \n117: func GetAgentRuntime(lister AgentRuntimeLister, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n118: \tif lister == nil {\n119: \t\treturn nil, ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound\n120: \t}\n121: \tar, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n122: \tif err != nil {\n123: \t\treturn nil, ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound\n124: \t}\n125: \treturn ar, nil\n126: }\n127: \n128: func GetCodeInterpreter(lister CodeInterpreterLister, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n129: \tif lister == nil {\n130: \t\treturn nil, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound\n131: \t}\n132: \tci, err := lister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)\n133: \tif err != nil {\n134: \t\treturn nil, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound\n135: \t}\n136: \treturn ci, nil\n137: }\n138: \n139: func (p *SandboxProcessor) BuildSandboxObject(runtime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n140: \tsuffix, err := RandString(8)\n141: \tif err != nil {\n142: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate random suffix: %w\", err)\n143: \t}\n144: \n145: \tsandboxName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", runtime.Name, suffix)\n146: \n147: \tlabels := map[string]string{}\n148: \tfor k, v := range runtime.Labels {\n149: \t\tlabels[k] = v\n150: \t}\n151: \tlabels[SessionIDLabelKey] = sessionID\n152: \n153: \tannotations := map[string]string{}\n154: \tfor k, v := range runtime.Annotations {\n155: \t\tannotations[k] = v\n156: \t}\n157: \n158: \tnow := time.Now()\n159: \tshutdownTime := now.Add(8 * time.Hour)\n160: \n161: \tcontainer := map[string]interface{}{\n162: \t\t\"name\":  \"agent-runtime\",\n163: \t\t\"image\": runtime.Spec.Container.Image,\n164: \t}\n165: \n166: \tif len(runtime.Spec.Container.Command) > 0 {\n167: \t\tcontainer[\"command\"] = runtime.Spec.Container.Command\n168: \t}\n169: \n170: \tif len(runtime.Spec.Container.Args) > 0 {\n171: \t\tcontainer[\"args\"] = runtime.Spec.Container.Args\n172: \t}\n173: \n174: \tif len(runtime.Spec.Container.Env) > 0 {\n175: \t\tenvBytes := make([]interface{}, len(runtime.Spec.Container.Env))\n176: \t\tfor i, envVar := range runtime.Spec.Container.Env {\n177: \t\t\tenvMap := map[string]interface{}{\"name\": envVar.Name}\n178: \t\t\tif envVar.Value != \"\" {\n179: \t\t\t\tenvMap[\"value\"] = envVar.Value\n180: \t\t\t}\n181: \t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom != nil {\n182: \t\t\t\tvalueFromMap := map[string]interface{}{}\n183: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.ConfigMapKeyRef != nil {\n184: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"configMapKeyRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n185: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": envVar.ValueFrom.ConfigMapKeyRef.Name,\n186: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"key\":  envVar.ValueFrom.ConfigMapKeyRef.Key,\n187: \t\t\t\t\t}\n188: \t\t\t\t}\n189: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef != nil {\n190: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"secretKeyRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n191: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": envVar.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef.Name,\n192: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"key\":  envVar.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef.Key,\n193: \t\t\t\t\t}\n194: \t\t\t\t}\n195: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.ResourceFieldRef != nil {\n196: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"resourceFieldRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n197: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"resource\":      envVar.ValueFrom.ResourceFieldRef.Resource,\n198: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"containerName\": envVar.ValueFrom.ResourceFieldRef.ContainerName,\n199: \t\t\t\t\t}\n200: \t\t\t\t}\n201: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.FieldRef != nil {\n202: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"fieldRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n203: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"fieldPath\": envVar.ValueFrom.FieldRef.FieldPath,\n204: \t\t\t\t\t}\n205: \t\t\t\t}\n206: \t\t\t\tenvMap[\"valueFrom\"] = valueFromMap\n207: \t\t\t}\n208: \t\t\tenvBytes[i] = envMap\n209: \t\t}\n210: \t\tcontainer[\"env\"] = envBytes\n211: \t}\n212: \n213: \tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{\n214: \t\tObject: map[string]interface{}{\n215: \t\t\t\"apiVersion\": \"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n216: \t\t\t\"kind\":       \"Sandbox\",\n217: \t\t\t\"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n218: \t\t\t\t\"name\":        sandboxName,\n219: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\":   runtime.Namespace,\n220: \t\t\t\t\"labels\":      labels,\n221: \t\t\t\t\"annotations\": annotations,\n222: \t\t\t},\n223: \t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n224: \t\t\t\t\"podTemplate\": map[string]interface{}{\n225: \t\t\t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n226: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"containers\": []interface{}{container},\n227: \t\t\t\t\t},\n228: \t\t\t\t},\n229: \t\t\t},\n230: \t\t\t\"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n231: \t\t\t\t\"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n232: \t\t\t},\n233: \t\t},\n234: \t}\n235: \n236: \treturn sandbox, nil\n237: }\n238: \n239: func (p *SandboxProcessor) BuildSandboxClaimObject(interpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n240: \tsuffix, err := RandString(8)\n241: \tif err != nil {\n242: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate random suffix: %w\", err)\n243: \t}\n244: \n245: \tclaimName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-claim-%s\", interpreter.Name, suffix)\n246: \n247: \tlabels := map[string]string{}\n248: \tfor k, v := range interpreter.Labels {\n249: \t\tlabels[k] = v\n250: \t}\n251: \tlabels[SessionIDLabelKey] = sessionID\n252: \n253: \tclaim := &unstructured.Unstructured{\n254: \t\tObject: map[string]interface{}{\n255: \t\t\t\"apiVersion\": \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n256: \t\t\t\"kind\":       \"SandboxClaim\",\n257: \t\t\t\"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n258: \t\t\t\t\"name\":      claimName,\n259: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\": interpreter.Namespace,\n260: \t\t\t\t\"labels\":    labels,\n261: \t\t\t},\n262: \t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{},\n263: \t\t},\n264: \t}\n265: \n266: \treturn claim, nil\n267: }\n268: \n269: func (p *SandboxProcessor) BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox(interpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n270: \tsuffix, err := RandString(8)\n271: \tif err != nil {\n272: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate random suffix: %w\", err)\n273: \t}\n274: \n275: \tsandboxName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", interpreter.Name, suffix)\n276: \n277: \tlabels := map[string]string{}\n278: \tfor k, v := range interpreter.Labels {\n279: \t\tlabels[k] = v\n280: \t}\n281: \tlabels[SessionIDLabelKey] = sessionID\n282: \n283: \tannotations := map[string]string{}\n284: \tfor k, v := range interpreter.Annotations {\n285: \t\tannotations[k] = v\n286: \t}\n287: \n288: \tnow := time.Now()\n289: \tshutdownTime := now.Add(8 * time.Hour)\n290: \n291: \tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{\n292: \t\tObject: map[string]interface{}{\n293: \t\t\t\"apiVersion\": \"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n294: \t\t\t\"kind\":       \"Sandbox\",\n295: \t\t\t\"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n296: \t\t\t\t\"name\":        sandboxName,\n297: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\":   interpreter.Namespace,\n298: \t\t\t\t\"labels\":      labels,\n299: \t\t\t\t\"annotations\": annotations,\n300: \t\t\t},\n301: \t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n302: \t\t\t\t\"podTemplate\": map[string]interface{}{\n303: \t\t\t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n304: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"containers\": []interface{}{\n305: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tmap[string]interface{}{\n306: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\":  \"code-interpreter\",\n307: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"image\": interpreter.Spec.Image,\n308: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n309: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n310: \t\t\t\t\t},\n311: \t\t\t\t},\n312: \t\t\t},\n313: \t\t\t\"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n314: \t\t\t\t\"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n315: \t\t\t},\n316: \t\t},\n317: \t}\n318: \n319: \treturn sandbox, nil\n320: }\n321: \n322: func (p *SandboxProcessor) resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error) {\n323: \tpodName := sandboxName\n324: \n325: \tpod, err := p.podLister.Pods(sandboxNamespace).Get(podName)\n326: \tif err == nil {\n327: \t\tif pod.Status.Phase != corev1.PodRunning {\n328: \t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s is not running (phase: %s)\", podName, pod.Status.Phase)\n329: \t\t}\n330: \t\tif pod.Status.PodIP == \"\" {\n331: \t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s has no IP assigned\", podName)\n332: \t\t}\n333: \t\treturn pod.Status.PodIP, nil\n334: \t}\n335: \n336: \tselector := labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\n337: \t\tSandboxNameLabelKey: sandboxName,\n338: \t})\n339: \n340: \tpodList, err := p.podLister.Pods(sandboxNamespace).List(selector)\n341: \tif err != nil {\n342: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list pods: %w\", err)\n343: \t}\n344: \n345: \tfor _, pod := range podList {\n346: \t\tfor _, ownerRef := range pod.OwnerReferences {\n347: \t\t\tif ownerRef.Kind == \"Sandbox\" && ownerRef.Name == sandboxName {\n348: \t\t\t\tif pod.Status.Phase != corev1.PodRunning {\n349: \t\t\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s is not running (phase: %s)\", pod.Name, pod.Status.Phase)\n350: \t\t\t\t}\n351: \t\t\t\tif pod.Status.PodIP == \"\" {\n352: \t\t\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s has no IP assigned\", pod.Name)\n353: \t\t\t\t}\n354: \t\t\t\treturn pod.Status.PodIP, nil\n355: \t\t\t}\n356: \t\t}\n357: \t}\n358: \n359: \tfor _, pod := range podList {\n360: \t\tif pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning && pod.Status.PodIP != \"\" {\n361: \t\t\treturn pod.Status.PodIP, nil\n362: \t\t}\n363: \t}\n364: \n365: \treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"no pod found for sandbox %s\", sandboxName)\n366: }\n367: \n368: func BuildEntryPoints(podIP string, ports []types.TargetPort) []types.SandboxEntryPoint {\n369: \tvar entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint\n370: \n371: \tfor _, port := range ports {\n372: \t\tentryPoint := types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n373: \t\t\tPath:     port.PathPrefix,\n374: \t\t\tProtocol: port.Protocol,\n375: \t\t\tEndpoint: net.JoinHostPort(podIP, fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", port.Port)),\n376: \t\t}\n377: \t\tentryPoints = append(entryPoints, entryPoint)\n378: \t}\n379: \n380: \treturn entryPoints\n381: }\n382: \n383: func (p *SandboxProcessor) CreateSandbox(\n384: \tctx context.Context,\n385: \tsandbox *unstructured.Unstructured,\n386: \tisWarmPool bool,\n387: \tuserClient dynamic.ResourceInterface,\n388: \tsessionID string,\n389: ) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n390: \tsandboxName := sandbox.GetName()\n391: \tsandboxNamespace := sandbox.GetNamespace()\n392: \n393: \tworkloadName := sandboxName\n394: \tif idx := strings.LastIndex(sandboxName, \"-\"); idx > 0 {\n395: \t\tworkloadName = sandboxName[:idx]\n396: \t}\n397: \n398: \tinfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n399: \t\tSessionID:    sessionID,\n400: \t\tSandboxID:    sandboxName,\n401: \t\tSandboxName:  sandboxName,\n402: \t\tKind:         \"Sandbox\",\n403: \t\tNamespace:    sandboxNamespace,\n404: \t\tWorkloadName: workloadName,\n405: \t\tStatus:       \"pending\",\n406: \t\tCreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n407: \t\tUpdatedAt:    time.Now(),\n408: \t}\n409: \n410: \tif isWarmPool {\n411: \t\tinfo.Kind = \"SandboxClaim\"\n412: \t}\n413: \n414: \tcreateCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)\n415: \tdefer cancel()\n416: \n417: \t_, err := userClient.Create(createCtx, sandbox, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n418: \tif err != nil {\n419: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", err)\n420: \t}\n421: \n422: \trunningChan := make(chan struct{})\n423: \terrChan := make(chan error, 1)\n424: \n425: \tgo func() {\n426: \t\tfor {\n427: \t\t\tselect {\n428: \t\t\tcase <-createCtx.Done():\n429: \t\t\t\terrChan <- ErrSandboxCreationTimeout\n430: \t\t\t\treturn\n431: \t\t\tdefault:\n432: \t\t\t\tpod, err := p.podLister.Pods(sandboxNamespace).Get(sandboxName)\n433: \t\t\t\tif err == nil && pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning && pod.Status.PodIP != \"\" {\n434: \t\t\t\t\tclose(runningChan)\n435: \t\t\t\t\treturn\n436: \t\t\t\t}\n437: \t\t\t\ttime.Sleep(500 * time.Millisecond)\n438: \t\t\t}\n439: \t\t}\n440: \t}()\n441: \n442: \tselect {\n443: \tcase <-runningChan:\n444: \tcase err := <-errChan:\n445: \t\tp.rollback(ctx, userClient, sandboxName)\n446: \t\treturn nil, err\n447: \tcase <-time.After(2 * time.Minute):\n448: \t\tp.rollback(ctx, userClient, sandboxName)\n449: \t\treturn nil, ErrSandboxCreationTimeout\n450: \t}\n451: \n452: \tpodIP, err := p.resolvePodIP(ctx, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName)\n453: \tif err != nil {\n454: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to resolve pod IP: %w\", err)\n455: \t}\n456: \n457: \tinfo.PodIP = podIP\n458: \n459: \tports := []types.TargetPort{\n460: \t\t{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"},\n461: \t}\n462: \tinfo.EntryPoints = BuildEntryPoints(podIP, ports)\n463: \tinfo.Status = \"running\"\n464: \tinfo.UpdatedAt = time.Now()\n465: \n466: \treturn info, nil\n467: }\n468: \n469: func (p *SandboxProcessor) rollback(ctx context.Context, client dynamic.ResourceInterface, name string) {\n470: \tdeleteCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 30*time.Second)\n471: \tdefer cancel()\n472: \tclient.Delete(deleteCtx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n473: }\n\n(End of file - total 473 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package processor\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/rand\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"math/big\"\n\t\"net\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/labels\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/